.TH "clear_selection" 9 "clear_selection" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
clear_selection \- remove current selection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" clear_selection
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Remove the current selection highlight, if any from the console
holding the selection. The caller must hold the console lock.
